Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/4%tsp}.

Halve the @bell pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Slice into thin
strips.

Trim and thinly slice the @spring onions{2}. Quarter the
@chestnut mushrooms{150%g}.

Cut the @Tenderstem® broccoli{80%g} into thirds. Trim the @green beans{80%g}
and cut into thirds.

When your pan of water is boiling, add the @egg noodle nests{2} and bring back
to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{4%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #colander{}. Run the noodles under cold water to stop
them sticking together.

While the noodles cook, heat a drizzle of @oil{drizzle} in a large #frying pan{}
or #wok{} on high heat.

Once hot, add the mushrooms, pepper, green beans and broccoli. Stir-fry until
starting to soften, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Stir in the @ginger, garlic & lemongrass puree{15%g} and cook for ~{1%minute}.

Add the cooked noodles, @soy sauce{25%ml} and @sweet chilli sauce{96%ml} to
the veg pan with a splash of water if you feel it needs it.

Stir-fry until everything is combined and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Once cooked, divide the noodle stir-fry between your #serving bowls{} and cover
with #foil{} to keep warm.

If you're adding an egg, wipe out the (now empty) pan and pop back on high heat
with a drizzle of @olive oil{drizzle}. Use a #frying pan{} if you were using a
wok.

Once hot, crack in the @egg{2} (1 per person).

Cook until the egg white is cooked and the yolk is the firmness you desire,
~{4-5%minutes}. Lower the heat as needed.

When ready, top your noodles with the fried eggs (if using).

Scatter over the @salted peanuts{25%g} and spring onions to finish. Enjoy!

> TIP: Add a splash of water to help cook the veg if you feel it needs it.

> TIP: Run the noodles under cold water to stop them sticking together.

> TIP: Use a frying pan if you were using a wok for the eggs.